Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula's announced an extension for expired learners' and drivers' licences, licence disks and professional driving permits. If your licence expired after March until the end of this year, you are safe. Transport ministry spokesperson Ayanda Allie-Paine spoke to Sally Burdett. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Drivers' licenses that expired from 26 March 2020 to 31 December 2020 have been extended for a seven-month grace period. According to the latest Government Gazette, learners' licenses, driving license cards, temporary license cards and professional driving permits are deemed valid for a grace period ending 31 August 2021. READ: Centres instructed to correct driving licence backlog License discs are not included in the grace period. License renewals have been negatively affected by the lockdown, with centres struggling to handle backlogs of thousands of licenses. There have also been complaints about allocating slots for driving licence renewals.